	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kawas Thermal Power Station is located in Surat district, in the state of Gujarat, India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is managed and run by the &lt;strong&gt;National Thermal Power Corporation (NTPC).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The power plant consists of &lt;strong&gt;gas-based combined cycle power units. It was one of the early gas-based power plants in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The total installed capacity of&lt;strong&gt; Kawas Thermal Power Station is around 645 MW.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;power plant plays a crucial role in supplying electricity to the state of Gujarat, supporting various industries and households.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
